Definition: Identifies the type of document at hand, e.g. Laboratory report. Includes document name.
The status of the report. E.g., preliminary, final.
Date and optionally the time of issuing the document (according to the local implementation rules, this could be either the date of authoring or signing the document).
Language in which the document is written. Language is expressed by the ISO language code.
Date on which document was modified (date of most recent version)
Level of confidentiality of the document. Implicit value is normal.
